Alright boys time for a shortform bit of trivia on astrology.
As they didn't have advanced telescopes but staggeringly sophisticated systems of mapping heavenly bodies, the Greek, Egyptian, and Chaldean, effectively that whole chunk of the Mediterranean, they could only map planetary movement out to Saturn.
Within the astrological/Zodiacal symbolism that was formed by the mixture of the Greeks and Levantine groups, this meant that Saturn took on the role of a boundary-marker. Not only that, but that Saturn grew to hold connotations associated with time for his role as a god of harvest, and extensive mortal suffering for the esoteric role of a very cruel but wise teacher. Among others, there is a reason why Father Time is depicted along the same lines as most personifications of Saturn; an old man in white with his scythe and hourglass.
Even as things developed in further time, with writings coming out of the Islamic Golden Age Levant, Umayyad Spain, and Renaissance Italy, Saturn was never specifically evil, only unforgiving and a harbinger of mortal suffering, but also took up half of the learned ventures, splitting them with Mercury to form the two scholarly spheres, and the father of alchemists and other students of occult knowledge.
I could go into further explanation, but the long and short of it is that the 'black-cube=666=Jews=Saturn' thing is a tangle of different mythological sources that just makes sense on a surface level. Within the foundation myth of Western Esoterism, Saturn is still among the Archons/Celestial Spheres appointed to Earth and the woven destinies of Man by God, he is just within the position of being a negative pole to the Sun's positive, much like how Mars is meant to be disorder relative to Jupiter's order.
The Black Sun, like much of Esoteric Hitlerism, is a very recent invention incumbent on almost, if none, of this.
